{
  "page": "Lordsport",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #DEDEE2;\">Lordsport</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\nHarbor village</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Lordsport_HBO.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Lordsport HBO.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/63/Lordsport_HBO.jpg/350px-Lordsport_HBO.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"197\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/63/Lordsport_HBO.jpg/525px-Lordsport_HBO.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/63/Lordsport_HBO.jpg/700px-Lordsport_HBO.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Lordsport in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Pyke_(island)\" title=\"Pyke (island)\">Pyke</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Government</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Botley\" title=\"House Botley\">House Botley</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Ruler</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Sawane_Botley\" title=\"Sawane Botley\">Sawane Botley</a> (ACoK)<br />Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Germund_Botley\" title=\"Germund Botley\">Germund Botley</a> (ADwD)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Religion</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">Drowned God</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Iron_Islands.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"The Iron Islands and the location of Lordsport\"><img alt=\"The Iron Islands and the location of Lordsport\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bd/Iron_Islands.jpg/350px-Iron_Islands.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"240\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bd/Iron_Islands.jpg/525px-Iron_Islands.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/bd/Iron_Islands.jpg/700px-Iron_Islands.jpg 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 77.8%; left: 28.3%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -4px; top: -4px; width: 7px; font-size: 7px;\"><img alt=\"The Iron Islands and the location of Lordsport\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/7px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Lordsport\" width=\"7\" height=\"7\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/11px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/14px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size:&#160;%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; left: 0.5em; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\">Lordsport</span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> and the location of Lordsport<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>Lordsport</b> is the seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Botley\" title=\"House Botley\">House Botley</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Pyke_(island)\" title=\"Pyke (island)\">Pyke</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Located on the central northern shore of the isle,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> it is the largest town in the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Chapters_that_take_place_at_Lordsport\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chapters that take place at Lordsport</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Half the size of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Hewett%27s_Town\" title=\"Lord Hewett&#39;s Town\">Lord Hewett's Town</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Lordsport is located near a wooded point with <a href=\"/index.php/Pine\" title=\"Pine\">pine</a>-clad bluffs. Lordsport provides safe anchor for those who wish to reach the castle of <a href=\"/index.php/Pyke\" title=\"Pyke\">Pyke</a>, seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">House Greyjoy</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Otter_Gimpknee%27s_inn\" title=\"Otter Gimpknee&#39;s inn\">Otter Gimpknee's inn</a> is located near the landing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The town is known for its forges and metalworkers, who produce excellent swords, axes, ringmail, and plate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Sigrin\" title=\"Sigrin\">Sigrin</a> is a prominent shipwright in Lordsport.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Botley\" title=\"House Botley\">House Botley</a> is a small square stone keep atop a hill overlooking the town; the banners of the Botleys droop from the castle's squat corner towers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">House Hoare</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Iron_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Iron Islands\">Kings of the Iron Islands</a>, ships from Lordsport began to trade at <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> sailed to Oldtown, Lannisport, and Lordsport when he was a young man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Greyjoy%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Greyjoy&#39;s Rebellion\">Greyjoy's Rebellion</a>, the timber-and-wattle castle of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Botley\" title=\"House Botley\">House Botley</a> and the village of Lordsport <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Lordsport\" title=\"Battle at Lordsport\">were razed</a> by the forces of King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a> before the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Pyke\" title=\"Battle at Pyke\">battle at Pyke</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After the war, Lordsport was rebuilt by its <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>, who used the stones from the burned remnants and cut new thatch for their roofs. <a href=\"/index.php/Otter_Gimpknee%27s_inn\" title=\"Otter Gimpknee&#39;s inn\">Otter Gimpknee's inn</a> at the harbor doubled in size. The <a href=\"/index.php/Sept\" title=\"Sept\">sept</a> was not rebuilt, however, as the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironmen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ironmen\">ironmen</a> prefer the <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">Drowned God</a> over the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, the religion of the victorious Robert.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Sawane_Botley\" title=\"Sawane Botley\">Sawane Botley</a> rebuilt his stronghold in stone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Returning to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> for the first time since <a href=\"/index.php/Greyjoy%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Greyjoy&#39;s Rebellion\">Greyjoy's Rebellion</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> sails on the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Myraham\" title=\"Myraham\">Myraham</a></i> from <a href=\"/index.php/Seagard\" title=\"Seagard\">Seagard</a> to Lordsport. Theon, the heir of <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon Greyjoy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"Lord of the Iron Islands\">Lord of the Iron Islands</a>, is displeased that the merchants of Lordsport do not recognize him. <a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Damphair</a> escorts his nephew from Lordsport to Pyke.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Balon musters <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> longships to Lordsport in preparation for his invasion of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Balon prevents merchant vessels like the <i>Myraham</i> from leaving the harbor and informing the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_lands\" title=\"Green lands\">green lands</a> of the gathering of ironborn ships.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Theon acquires a horse, <a href=\"/index.php/Smiler\" title=\"Smiler\">Smiler</a>, from <a href=\"/index.php/Sawane_Botley\" title=\"Sawane Botley\">Sawane Botley</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Lordsport\" title=\"Lord of Lordsport\">Lord of Lordsport</a>, and takes on the mute <a href=\"/index.php/Wex_Pyke\" title=\"Wex Pyke\">Wex Pyke</a>, the bastard of Sawane's half-brother <a href=\"/index.php/Sargon_Botley\" title=\"Sargon Botley\">Sargon</a>, as his squire.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Theon sees his newly-built longship, later named <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sea_Bitch\" title=\"Sea Bitch\">Sea Bitch</a></i>, on the strand of Lordsport. <a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a>, calling herself \"Esgred\" and claiming to be the daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrode\" title=\"Ambrode\">Ambrode</a> and wife of <a href=\"/index.php/Sigrin\" title=\"Sigrin\">Sigrin</a>, escorts her unknowing brother from the town to Pyke, where she reveals her true identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The captain of the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Myraham\" title=\"Myraham\">Myraham</a></i> reports that <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Greyjoy</a> sailed into Lordsport's harbor the day after the death of his brother Balon, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_North\" title=\"King of the Isles and the North\">King of the Isles and the North</a>. Euron claimed the <a href=\"/index.php/Seastone_Chair\" title=\"Seastone Chair\">Seastone Chair</a> at Pyke and drowned Lord Botley in a cask of seawater when he objected.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>It is reported that Euron had Sawane killed because he recognized Balon's heir to be Theon, not Euron.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Ralf_of_Lordsport\" title=\"Ralf of Lordsport\">Ralf of Lordsport</a> comes from the town, whose new lord is <a href=\"/index.php/Germund_Botley\" title=\"Germund Botley\">Germund Botley</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Asha, a claimant to the Seastone Chair, intends to restore Lordsport to Sawane's son and heir, her childhood friend <a href=\"/index.php/Tristifer_Botley\" title=\"Tristifer Botley\">Tristifer Botley</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>There are many fine metalworkers amongst the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a>, as might be expected; the forges of Lordsport produce swords, axes, ringmail, and plate second to none.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Beneath the dubious protection of the fish-ridden little castle lay the village of Lordsport, its harbor aswarm with ships. When last he'd seen Lordsport, it had been a smoking wasteland, the skeletons of burnt longships and smashed galleys littering the stony shore like the bones of dead <a href=\"/index.php/Leviathan\" title=\"Leviathan\">leviathans</a>, the houses no more than broken walls and cold ashes. After ten years, few traces of <a href=\"/index.php/Greyjoy%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Greyjoy&#39;s Rebellion\">the war</a> remained. The <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> had built new hovels with the stones of the old, and cut fresh sod for their roofs. <a href=\"/index.php/Otter_Gimpknee%27s_inn\" title=\"Otter Gimpknee&#39;s inn\">A new inn</a> had risen beside the landing, twice the size of the old one, with a lower story of cut stone and two upper stories of timber. The <a href=\"/index.php/Sept\" title=\"Sept\">sept</a> beyond had never been rebuilt, though; only a seven-sided foundation remained where it had stood. <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert Baratheon's</a> fury had soured the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironmen's</a> taste for the <a href=\"/index.php/New_gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New gods\">new gods</a>, it would seem.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Among the masts of countless fishing boats, he spied a <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyroshi</a> trading galley off-loading beside a lumbering <a href=\"/index.php/Ibbenese\" title=\"Ibbenese\">Ibbenese</a> cog with her black-tarred hull. A great number of longships, fifty or sixty at the least, stood out to sea or lay beached on the pebbled shore to the north.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lordsport has no lack of strong arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> to \"<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Esgred</a>\"</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tristifer</b>: The <a href=\"/index.php/Silence\" title=\"Silence\">Silence</a> returned with holds full of treasure. Plate and <a href=\"/index.php/Pearl\" title=\"Pearl\">pearls</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Emerald\" title=\"Emerald\">emeralds</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Ruby\" title=\"Ruby\">rubies</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sapphire\" title=\"Sapphire\">sapphires</a> big as eggs, bags of <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">coin</a> so heavy that no man can lift them ... the <a href=\"/index.php/Crow%27s_Eye\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crow&#39;s Eye\">Crow's Eye</a> has been buying friends at every hand. My uncle <a href=\"/index.php/Germund_Botley\" title=\"Germund Botley\">Germund</a> calls himself <a href=\"/index.php/House_Botley\" title=\"House Botley\">Lord Botley</a> now, and rules in Lordsport as your uncle's man.<br />\n<b>Asha</b>: You are the rightful Lord Botley. Once I hold the <a href=\"/index.php/Seastone_Chair\" title=\"Seastone Chair\">Seastone Chair</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sawane_Botley\" title=\"Sawane Botley\">your father's</a> lands shall be restored.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Tristifer_Botley\" title=\"Tristifer Botley\">Tristifer Botley</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chapters_that_take_place_at_Lordsport\">Chapters that take place at Lordsport</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Chapters that take place at Lordsport\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 11\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i>: 11. Theon I</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_24\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 24\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i>: 24. Theon II</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lordsport&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafmap_of_the_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Map of the Iron Islands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\">2.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\">2.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\">2.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\">2.8</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-9\">2.9</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Clash 